</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/dezeen/~4/zZP750XUtq8" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:22:"http://www.dezeen.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:6:"Dezeen";}s:32:"e99a78b620504fe4d88872e7644ffcbf";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:76:"The cost of a botched operation? £6.99 on Steam thanks to Surgeon Simulator";s:4:"link";s:62:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/surgeon-simulator-on-steam/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Steve Dent";s:4:"date";i:1366349100;s:7:"content";s:1527:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/surgeon-simulator-on-steam/"><img alt="Torment patients for yourself with Surgeon Simulator, now on Steam for 699" data-src-height="340" data-src-width="620" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/surgeon-simulator-steam-04-19-13-01.jpg"></a></p><p> Clumsy wannabe sawbones: warm up your hammers and hatchets, because Surgeon Simulator has arrived on Steam. The <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/28/surgeon-simulator-2013-passes-through-steams-greenlight-program/">infamous game</a> challenges players to save patients' lives with an array of coarse tools and an apparent case of the DTs, and was prototyped in a mere 48 hours during the Global Game Jam back in January. After being <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/greenlight/">greenlit</a> by Steam, it's now up for grabs at &pound;6.99 (about $11) with extra features like a "fiendishly difficult ambulance mode" that brings extra quarts of gore, along with new operations like a kidney or brain transplant and a new soundtrack and visuals. There's a lineup of desperate patients -- they'd have to be -- waiting at the source link and the video after the break.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/gaming/" rel="tag">Gaming</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/surgeon-simulator-on-steam/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="http://www.surgeonsimulator2013.com/" target="_blank">Bossa Studios</a><!--//--></p>";s: