/tr></table></div><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163067893325/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae4a849/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163067893325/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae4a849/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163067893325/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae4a849/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/e40dADbnzyY" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"03002d8baaa730cd6018694d3e2c0220";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:82:"Nokia Lumia teaser asks 'what can the matter be?', puts Malaysians on edge (video)";s:4:"link";s:59:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/nokia-lumia-ad-malaysia/";s:6:"author";s:11:"Sharif Sakr";s:4:"date";i:1366335300;s:7:"content";s:2071:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/nokia-lumia-ad-malaysia/"><img alt="Nokia Lumia ad asks 'what can the matter be', puts Malaysians on edge" data-src-height="360" data-src-width="619" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/lumia-ad.jpg"></a></p><p> Flickering hospital lights. A man going ballistic in a padded cell. A hooded ghoul. These are the images Nokia Malaysia wants to put into our heads in the run-up to a mysterious Lumia-related launch coming on April 25th. That date has also been linked to Verizon's launch of the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/05/nokia-lumia-928-spied-for-verizon/">Lumia 928</a>, but we're not sure how that might be relevant. Alternatively, it could be a countdown to the Malaysian launch of the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/25/nokia-lumia-720-preview/">Lumia 720</a> or <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/25/nokia-lumia-520-hands-on/">Lumia 520</a>. The thing is, we're intimately familiar with both those handsets and neither can be described as even remotely spooky. Unless it's another <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/05/28/batman-themed-nokia-lumia-900-coming-soon-utility-belt-clip-not/">Batman Edition</a>?</p><p> <strong>Update:</strong> The video on Nokia's official YouTube channel has been pulled. We've added a different embed in the hope of preserving this curious piece of marketing for future generations.</p><p> <br> [Thanks, Piaget]</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/nokia/" rel="tag">Nokia</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/nokia-lumia-ad-malaysia/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=oqxnGB1zIjg" target="_blank">Nokia Malaysia (YouTube)</a><!--//-->, <a href="http://www.lumialivecentre.com/" target="_blank">LumiaLiveCentre.com</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"47b1dff59ede5eeb79471a93e7689793";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:39:"City Vision Mag - Sick &amp;amp; Wonder";s:4:"link";s:66:"http://www.behance.net/gallery/City-Vision-Mag-Sick-Wonder/7364427";s:6:"author";s:0:"";s:4:"date";i:1366335001;s:7:"content";s:190:"<img src="http://behance.vo.llnwd.net/profiles12/1550221/projects/7364427/c98696b4aa846e21169ce17854ca40ee.jpg"><br> Illustrations for City Vision Magazine, Issue 8, titled Sick &amp; Wonder";s:9:"feed_link";s:23:"http://www.behance.net/";s:10:"feed_title";s:25:"Behance Featured Projects";}s:32:"cfb0bf0f189740f8a0248fa249a8239e";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:67:"'Vampire Diaries': Senior Prom Brings Out the Worst in Mystic Falls";s:4:"link";s:96:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/BK1jG16RYRw/vampire-diaries-recap-pictures-you-442263";s:6:"author";s:11:"Philiana Ng";s:4:"date";i:1366333740;s:7:"content";s:1803:"<img src="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/sites/default/files/2013/04/vampire_diaries_pictures_of_you_dobrev_a_l.jpg"><br>On Thursday's return 