</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/thr/news/~4/1DEdthzzbAM" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:33:"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:18:"Hollywood Reporter";}s:32:"29030fcef12ceb6f7c9ce90edb707185";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:69:"Twitter UK's #Flock cuckoo clock shares time and tweets alike (video)";s:4:"link";s:96:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/twitter-uk-flock-cuckoo-clock-tells-us-about-time-and-tweets/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1366327860;s:7:"content";s:1976:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/twitter-uk-flock-cuckoo-clock-tells-us-about-time-and-tweets/"><img alt="Twitter UK's #Flock cuckoo clock tells us of both time and tweets video" data-src-height="340" data-src-width="620" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/twitter-flock-clock.jpg"></a></p><p> The concept of a Twitter-aware cuckoo clock has <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2010/04/22/twitwee-clock-checks-tweets-with-old-world-charm/">certainly been done</a> -- just not by Twitter itself, until now. Twitter UK has teamed up with Berg to produce #Flock, a smarter-than-average clock that both marks time and pops out a bird whenever there are new followers, replies and retweets. It's comparatively simple underneath the wood, as a <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/08/14/berg-little-printer-up-for-preorder/">Berg Cloud</a> developer kit links an arm mechanism to the owner's Twitter account. The trick will be owning one in the first place. As much as we'd like Twitter to sell #Flock on a general basis, the company is giving away its hand-built creation only to companies and people that "push the creative boundaries," which will mostly involve advertisers rather than any of <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/06/engadget-ces-twitter/">us common folk</a>.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/household/" rel="tag">Household</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/internet/" rel="tag">Internet</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/19/twitter-uk-flock-cuckoo-clock-tells-us-about-time-and-tweets/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/4/18/4239408/twitter-uk-shows-off-flock-a-cuckoo-clock-powered-by-tweets">The Verge</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/TwitterAdsUK/status/324897687004663808">Twitter Ads UK (Twitter)</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"90626c3f573a9623477d2ae168ed26f0";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:71:"'Vampire Diaries': Trailer for 'The Originals' Spinoff Hits Web (Video)";s:4:"link";s:103:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/BrbBygl75v8/vampire-diaries-trailer-originals-spinoff-442287";s:6:"author";s:11:"Philiana Ng";s:4:"date";i:1366326964;s:7:"content";s:1730:"<img src="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/sites/default/files/2013/04/vampire_diaries_joseph_morgan_a_l.jpg"><br>The backdoor pilot, centered on the Original family in New Orleans, will air April 25.<p><a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/vampire-diaries-trailer-originals-spinoff-442287" target="_blank">read more</a></p><div>
