r Life Yet" href="http://gizmodo.com/space/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">space</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read NASA Just Found the Two Most Perfect Planets for Life Yet" href="http://gizmodo.com/5995005/nasa-just-found-the-two-most-perfect-planets-for-life-yet"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read NASA Just Found the Two Most Perfect Planets for Life Yet" alt="Click here to read NASA Just Found the Two Most Perfect Planets for Life Yet" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18l1divtd8zzyjpg/xlarge.jpg"></a></div> </div> Ever feel like you're all alone in this big, ol' universe? Don't. Because NASA has just discovered two prime planet candidates that fulfill nearly every condition necessary to life that we're aware of. And according to William Borucki, chief scientist for NASA's Kepler telescope, these two are the best bets we've ever found. <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5995005/nasa-just-found-the-two-most-perfect-planets-for-life-yet" title="Click here to read more about NASA Just Found the Two Most Perfect Planets for Life Yet">More&nbsp;&raquo;</a> <br><img width="1" height="1" src="http://gizmodo.feedsportal.com/c/34976/f/647164/s/2ae268d7/mf.gif" border="0"><div><table border="0"><tr><td valign="middle"><a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995005%2Fnasa-just-found-the-two-most-perfect-planets-for-life-yet&amp;t=NASA+Just+Found+the+Two+Most+Perfect+Planets+for+Life+Yet" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995005%2Fnasa-just-found-the-two-most-perfect-planets-for-life-yet&amp;t=NASA+Just+Found+the+Two+Most+