ompany+Just+Made+Vibrating+Underwear+Controlled+by+Your+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995000%2Fuh-a-condom-company-just-made-vibrating-underwear-controlled-your-iphones&amp;t=Uh%2C+A+Condom+Company+Just+Made+Vibrating+Underwear+Controlled+by+Your+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995000%2Fuh-a-condom-company-just-made-vibrating-underwear-controlled-your-iphones&amp;t=Uh%2C+A+Condom+Company+Just+Made+Vibrating+Underwear+Controlled+by+Your+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995000%2Fuh-a-condom-company-just-made-vibrating-underwear-controlled-your-iphones&amp;t=Uh%2C+A+Condom+Company+Just+Made+Vibrating+Underwear+Controlled+by+Your+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5995000%2Fuh-a-condom-company-just-made-vibrating-underwear-controlled-your-iphones&amp;t=Uh%2C+A+Condom+Company+Just+Made+Vibrating+Underwear+Controlled+by+Your+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></div><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644649333/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae25d60/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644649333/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae25d60/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644649333/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ae25d60/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/Cu39EuOjV5c" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"dcd86e4d7cc58f877793a185786ec5cd";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:93:"Blackstone reportedly backs out of Dell deal, leaves bidding war to Icahn and company founder";s:4:"link";s:80:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/18/blackstone-reportedly-backs-out-of-dell-deal/";s:6:"author";s:12:"Sean Buckley";s:4:"date";i:1366311120;s:7:"content";s:2066:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/18/blackstone-reportedly-backs-out-of-dell-deal/"><img alt="Blackstone reportedly backs out of Dell deal, leaves bidding war to Icahn and company founder" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2008/09/dell-factory-09-05-08.jpg"></a></p><p> <span>Micheal Dell's battle to <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/05/dell-going-private-ms-loan/">take back his namesake</a> firm may have just become a little easier: Blackstone seems to have lost interest. According to the <em>Wall Street Journal</em>, the group has backed out of the bidding war for the computer maker, declining to comment on the matter. <em>Bloomberg</em> sources claim that Blackstone lost interest after peeking at the company's financials and were reportedly </span>disappointed <span>by the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/10/idc-pc-shipments-in-q1-faced-their-steepest-drop-known-to-date/">revenue outlook</a>. This leaves the company's founder to contend with only <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/23/potential-dell-bidding-war-afoot-as-blackstone-group-and-carl-ic/">Carl Icahn</a>, giving his original $24.4 billion bid a better shot at acceptance. The jury's still out on <em>who</em> Dell's next owner will be, but at least it's a little less complicated now, right? </span></p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/desktops/" rel="tag">Desktops</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/laptops/" rel="tag">Laptops</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/dell/" rel="tag">Dell</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/18/blackstone-reportedly-backs-out-of-dell-deal/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://online.wsj.com/article_email/SB10001424127887323809304578431513006541432-lMyQjAxMTAzMDEwODExNDgyWj.html">Wall Street Journal</a><!--//-->, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-19/blackstone-said-to-pull-out-of-dell-bid-on-plummeting-pc-sales.html">Bloomberg</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"324959a3563bb9a538467847b68aa01e";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:74:"Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything";s:4:"link";s:128:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/K0cMm_mt5Cw/dedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything";s:6:"author";s:16:"Andrew Liszewski";s:4:"date";i:1366310400;s:7:"content";s:4079:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything" href="http://gizmodo.com/fast-food/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">fastfood</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything" href="http://gizmodo.com/5994991/dedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything" alt="Click here to read Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18l13dbdc08wkjpg/xlarge.jpg"></a></div> </div> Resisting the temptation to dig into your french fries after leaving the drive through at McDonald's takes discipline that only a handful of monks on Earth possess. And McDonald's Japan just wants you to stop fighting the urge altogether with the introduction of the <a href="http://www.mcd-holdings.co.jp/news/2013/promotion/promo0417a.html">potato holder</a> that makes it easy to perch your large fries in your vehicle's cup holders. <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5994991/dedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything" title="Click here to read more about Dedicated McDonald's French Fry Holders Should Come Standard in Everything">More&nbsp;&raquo;</a> <br><img width="1" height="1" src="http://gizmodo.feedsportal.com/c/34976/f/647164/s/2ae25a08/mf.gif" border="0"><div><table border="0"><tr><td valign="middle"><a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994991%2Fdedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything&amp;t=Dedicated+McDonald%27s+French+Fry+Holders+Should+Come+Standard+in+Everything" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994991%2Fdedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything&amp;t=Dedicated+McDonald%27s+French+Fry+Holders+Should+Come+Standard+in+Everything" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994991%2Fdedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-come-standard-in-everything&amp;t=Dedicated+McDonald%27s+French+Fry+Holders+Should+Come+Standard+in+Everything" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994991%2Fdedicated-mcdonalds-french-fry-holders-should-c