;s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1366307460;s:7:"content";s:2332:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/18/verizon-says-its-galaxy-s-4-is-coming-sometime-in-may/"><img alt="Verizon says its Galaxy S 4 is coming sometime in May" data-src-height="450" data-src-width="619" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/samsung-galaxy-s-4-verizon-pr-1366323265.jpg"></a></p><p> If you noticed that Verizon was silent while other US carriers provided their <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/17/samsung-galaxy-s-4-to-cost-150-at-both-t-mobile-and-sprint/">launch</a> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/17/samsung-galaxy-s-4-up-for-pre-order-at-us-cellular-for-200/">schedules</a> for the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/14/samsung-galaxy-s-4-preview/">Galaxy S 4</a>, you're not alone -- it was the only real holdout among the big four networks. As it turns out, the company was just continuing a small tradition of being <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2010/09/07/official-samsung-fascinate-launching-september-9/">fashionably</a> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/11/28/samsung-galaxy-note-ii-verizon/">late</a> with influential phones. Big Red now says its version of the Samsung flagship will appear sometime in May, skipping past the first wave of GS 4 releases later in April. An exact date? Pricing? Capacities? Those are coming at an unspecified point "soon," although that may not be soon enough for subscribers who have to own the latest and greatest.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/wireless/" rel="tag">Wireless</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/samsung/" rel="tag">Samsung</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/verizon/" rel="tag">Verizon</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/18/verizon-says-its-galaxy-s-4-is-coming-sometime-in-may/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a href="http://www.droid-life.com/2013/04/18/verizon-takes-to-twitter-to-confirm-its-version-of-the-galaxy-s4-arrives-in-may/" target="_blank">Droid-Life</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://twitter.com/VZWnews/status/324990966232645632" target="_blank">Verizon Wireless (Twitter)</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"4a3318600542e6c0a13c0bc04f3a1ab3";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:37:"Why Video Discovery Startups All Fail";s:4:"link";s:39:"http://cnet.tumblr.com/post/48287624886";s:6:"author";s:0:"";s:4:"date";i:1366306200;s:7:"content";s:278:"<a href="http://www.hunterwalk.com/2013/04/why-video-discovery-startups-all-fail.html">Why Video Discovery Startups All Fail</a>: <p>The former product head of YouTube <a href="http://www.hunterwalk.com/2013/04/why-video-discovery-startups-all-fail.html">explains</a>.&nbsp;</p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:23:"http://cnet.tumblr.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:4:"CNET";}s:32:"57ae695c40f4def5337244385c54a10a";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:47:"Shenzhen Stock Exchange by OMA nears completion";s:4:"link";s:53:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/dezeen/~3/9vlLv1LVfBw/";s:6:"author";s:12:"Amy Frearson";s:4:"date";i:1366304411;s:7:"content";s:1479:"<p><a href="http://www.dezeen.com/2013/04/18/shenzhen-stock-exchange-by-oma-nears-completion/">
